<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government May Reactivate Super-Phoenix Reactor </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801150794 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1400 
GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1801150794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A report has come out envisaging the reactivation, 
under certain conditions, of the Super-Phoenix [fast breeder 
reactor]. (Andre-Claude Lacoste) of the Nuclear Safety 
Directorate says in this report, which was submitted to the 
Industry and Environment Ministry this morning, that from the 
point of view of safety, the reactivation of the reactor could 
be authorized given two conditions: that the work on combating 
sodium leaks is completed successfully, and that the reactor is 
brought into service at reduced power for a few months. In other 
words, Super-Phoenix will be reactivated. 

</TEXT>

