<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Comments on Ciller Remarks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1901160194 Athens ET-1 Television Network in Greek 1300 
GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1901160194 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ET-1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Defense Minister Yerasimos Arsenis has said it is 
ridiculous for the Turks to believe Greece has aggressive plans 
because its defense doctrine is well known. Arsenis' comment 
came in response to Turkish Prime Minister Tansu Ciller's 
statement about Greek threats not enabling Turkey to 
demilitarize its western shores. The minister described Turkish 
verbal aggression as an awkward effort to attract international 
attention. He added there has been no increase in the number of 
airspace violations, which remain at the same level. He said 
Turkish planes are immediately intercepted. 
  On Saturday [22 January] the defense minister will meet 
Cypriot President Glavkos Kliridhis in Thessaloniki to discuss 
the joint Greek-Cypriot defense area. 

</TEXT>

