<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Spokesman Comments on CSCE Veto </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1901141794 Athens ET-1 Television Network in Greek 1300 
GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1901141794 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ET-1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos said if 
Skopje shows the goodwill Greece expects, the government could 
reexamine its veto on the state's accession to the CSCE. 
  [Begin Venizelos recording] If Skopje demonstrates the 
goodwill Greece has repeatedly sought--and still does, because 
this is an obligation derived from international law--then the 
Greek Government could reexamine the veto on Skopje joining the 
CSCE. [end recording] 
  Venizelos added that Greece is ready for talks with Skopje 
within the UN framework, but on the basis determined by the 
government. Commenting on remarks Alternate Foreign Minister 
Theodhoros Pangalos made on Skopje yesterday, Venizelos stressed 
that as Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou said, he and Foreign 
Minister Karolos Papoulias are handling the issue. 
  The spokesman stressed that the issue is being raised on 
many 
levels, and recalled that it was recently raised on the highest 
possible level, the NATO summit. He said the prime minister had 
the opportunity to utilize one advantage of the European Union 
Presidency. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

