<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Stresses Need To Restructure Defense </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1901071594 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 0530 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1901071594 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Greek Defense Minister Yerasimos Arsenis said the 
old danger from the East and the new situation in the Balkans 
require Greece to restructure its defense doctrine to 
effectively defend the country from old and new dangers. 
  In an address at the Larisa headquarters, Arsenis discussed 
immediately implementing the new program. He said it would soon 
change the structure and meaning of national defense. Arsenis 
said: At the very most, the goal is to create Armed Forces that 
will be well prepared for war and will be ruled with meritocracy. 

</TEXT>

