<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pangalos Meets Visiting Australian Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1701193694 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1800 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1701193694 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Alternate Foreign Minister Theodhoros Pangalos today 
met with Australian Foreign Minister Gareth Evans, who is 
visiting Greece, and discussed issues on improving 
Australian-European Union [EU] relations. 
  Evans said he is not very satisfied with Australia's 
cooperation with the EU. Pangalos said Greece would have wanted 
to import cheaper products from Australia instead of more 
expensive ones from EU member states because of communal 
solidarity. 

</TEXT>

