<H3> <TI>   U.S. Sends Message to Cetin on `Terrorist' Group </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1801162994 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1445 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1801162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Jan 18 (AA) -- The United States Secretary 
of State Warren Christopher on Tuesday [18 January] sent a 
message to Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin saying that the 
outlawed separatist terrorist organization should be hold in a 
mechanism that will be set up between the U.S. and Syrian 
foreign ministers. [sentence as received] 
  Christopher speaking on a meeting between the U.S. President 
Bill Clinton and Syrian Head of State Hafiz al-Asad in Geneva 
said that Clinton had warned al-Asad on the support Syria is 
giving to terrorist organization. 
  The U.S. President had qualified the outlawed organization 
as 
the number one terror organization adding that his country and 
Syria had important differences on the issue. 

</TEXT>

