<H3> <TI>   Russian Deputy Energy Minister Concludes Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1801122694 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1100 
GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1801122694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Anatoliy Tikhonov, Russian deputy minister for fuel 
and energy, has said Russia can supply Turkey's natural gas 
needs up to the year 2050. 
  Tikhonov made a statement at Istanbul Ataturk Airport before 
departing at the end of his visit to Turkey. He said Russia 
annually supplies Turkey with 5.5 billion cubic meters of 
natural gas, adding that this amount will be increased by 2.5 
billion cubic meters beginning in 1996. Pointing out that his 
visit has been very beneficial, Tikhonov said a protocol has 
been signed on cooperation in the fields of oil, natural gas, 
and coal. He concluded by saying that the conditions are 
conducive for further cooperation between the Turkish and 
Russian energy complexes. 

</TEXT>

