<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Natural Gas Contracts Signed With Turkmenistan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1701191594 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1800 
GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1701191594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] A contract has been signed with Turkmenistan to buy 
up to 15 billion cubic meters of natural gas. Also the pipeline 
that will carry the natural gas from that country to Europe will 
pass through Turkey. 
  BOTAS [Pipeline and Petroleum Transport Corporation] 
Director 
General Hayrettin Uzun held a news conference in Ankara where he 
said that with the contract, Turkey will no longer be dependent 
on only one source for its natural gas. Also, he said, the 
contract will supply our demand for natural gas. 
  Uzun said that BOTAS wants to be included in the consortium 
that is being set up to build the pipeline that will deliver the 
natural gas from Turkmenistan to Western Europe. An agreement 
will be signed on our participation in the committee, he said. 
  Also, talks are under way to increase the 6 billion cubic 
meters of natural gas Turkey buys from Russia per year to 10.5 
billion cubic meters. 

</TEXT>

