<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Welcomes Claes Remarks on EU </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1801130294 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1000 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1801130294 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Cypriot Government has welcomed Belgian Foreign 
Minister Willy Claes' statement, which says that if there is no 
clear indication of a Cyprus solution by January 1995, the 
negotiations for Cyprus' accession to the European Union [EU] 
will begin immediately. Speaking to the Cyprus Broadcasting 
Corporation, Foreign Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis described this 
position as very positive. Claes made his remarks during a 
meeting of the Council of Europe's Political Committee, which he 
chairs. Claes also made it clear that the EU observer to the 
Cyprus issue negotiations will report directly to EU Commission 
President Jacques Delors. 

</TEXT>

