<H3> <TI>   European Presidency Issues Press Release on Congo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1301140994 Brussels RAPID Database in English 13 Jan 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1301140994 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels RAPID Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [EC press release No. PRES/94/001: "Press Statement by the </F>
Presidency on Behalf of The European Union"] 
  [Text] The European Union is following with concern 
developments in the situation in the Congo, particularly in the 
increasing frequency of confrontations in the capital and the 
weakening of the process established by the Libreville Agreement 
of 4 August 1993. 
  The European Union would remind the Congolese parties 
concerned that it was asked to participate in implementation of 
the agreement, inter alia by making magistrates available to the 
Congo for the arbitration board. The board's careful and 
independent work cannot be called into question and the European 
Union would find it impossible to understand any contesting of 
its decisions. 
  The European Union urges all Congolese political forces to 
respect the provisions of the Libreville Agreement and seek a 
political solution to the crisis through dialogue. 

</TEXT>

