<F P=106> [Article signed BVP, PDJ: "Eddy Baldewijns New President </F>
Flemish Council;" as released by Brussels BELGA Database] 
  [Text] Brussels, 3 Jan (BELGA) -- The Flemish Parliament on 
Thursday [13 January] appointed socialist Eddy Baldwijns from 
Limburg as its new president. He replaces fellow party member 
Louis Vanvelthoven, who resigned because of links to a case of 
fraudulent examinations in the assembly. 
  In his first speech as president, Baldewijns pleaded that a 
code of ethics be established for all elected representatives. 
His opponent was Vlaams Blok Representative Marijke Dillen. 
Baldewijns received 121 of the 142 votes. Although the Vlaams 
Blok group has only 17 members, 19 members of parliament voted 
for Dillen. 

