<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kinkel, Russian Commander Discuss Troop Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1801153494 Hamburg DPA in German 1446 GMT 18 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1801153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- Russian troops will complete their 
withdrawal from eastern Germany as agreed by the end of August, 
Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel (FDP) and Colonel General Matvey 
Burlakov, commander in chief of the Western Group of Russian 
Forces in Germany, stressed in Bonn today. At the 11th session 
of the mixed German-Russian commission, Kinkel emphasized the 
organizational skills of the Russian Western Group of Forces and 
that the remaining 31,436 men would return home by August. A 
spokesman also said the problems described by Burlakov relating 
to the regional allocation and completion of the soldiers' 
accommodation in Russia, which is being financed by the German 
government, would in no way delay the withdrawal schedule. 

</TEXT>

