<H3> <TI>   Kinkel Doubts Bosnia Willing To Work for Peace </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1301111794 Hamburg DPA in German 0923 GMT 13 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1301111794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- Following the failure of last 
weekend's Croatian-Bosnian Petersberg conference, Foreign 
Minister Klaus Kinkel has said he seriously doubts the various 
sides' willingness for peace. During talks with the American UN 
Ambassador Madeleine Albright late last night, Kinkel said that 
we have to "seriously ask ourselves to what degree the 
conflicting parties are currently driven by a genuine desire for 
peace," the Foreign Ministry announced today. In this context, 
Kinkel referred to the Muslim offensive against areas to which 
the Croats are entitled. 

