<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government, Iranian Officials Meet in Bonn </TI></H3>
<H4>   Iranian Official Comments </H4>
<F P=102> LD1101225794 Hamburg DPA in German 2051 GMT 11 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1101225794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Bonn (DPA) -- Helmut Szimkus, the German who has 
been sentenced to death in Iran, can hope for a pardon. The 
influential Iranian politician Mohamad Javad [Larijani] today 
referred to the right of the religious leader 'Ali Khamene'i to 
grant a pardon. [passage omitted] 
  Speaking to journalists this evening, Larijani said a pardon 
is part of Iranian law. The procedure prescribes a detailed 
examination of the case. Should Khamene'i use his right to 
grant a pardon in the Szimkus case, this would happen in three 
to four months at the earliest. 
  The Iranian politician stressed that he did not bring up the 
so-called "Mykonos trial" in Berlin. [passage omitted] 
  Larijani expressed his hope that, despite the difficulties, 
German-Iranian relations will continue to develop in a positive 
way and that a solution can be found for Iran's current problems 
in meeting its financial obligations. The German refusal to 
resume the construction of the Bushehr nuclear power station on 
the Persian Gulf, which was suspended 14 years ago, is a "very 
negative point," he said. 
  The politician also warned against further "politicizing" 
the 
death sentence (`Fatwa') Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeyni, the 
deceased leader of the revolution, issued against the writer 
Salman Rushdie. Rushdie has offended millions of Muslims with 
his book The Satanic Verses. "The more the case of 
Rushdie is politicized, the more it will stir the emotions of 
the Muslims," he said. 
  The politician also criticized the Israeli-Palestinian peace 
process, saying it is neither fair nor feasible. He said a 
large majority of Palestinians reject the Gaza-Jericho agreement. 

</TEXT>

