Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel 
met in Bonn on Friday [14 January] with Mohamad Javad Larijani, 
a leading Iranian politician. During the meeting, the fate of 
Helmut Szimkus, the German who is under sentence of death in 
Iran, was probably discussed. There have been growing 
indications over the last few days that as a result of pressure 
from the German Government, Szimkus, who was sentenced for 
spying for Iraq, can hope for a pardon. 
  Larijani, who belongs to Iran's Supreme Defense Council and 
plays a leading role in parliament in Tehran, ended a five-day 
visit to Germany on Friday. He headed a small delegation of 
Iranian parliamentarians that held talks concerning the 
development of German-Iranian relations with the government, the 
Bundestag, and companies. The meeting with Kinkel was not 
originally on their schedule. 

