<H3> <TI>   Government Approves Further Budget Cuts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701183794 Hamburg DPA in German 1808 GMT 17 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1701183794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- A government meeting on public 
expenditure chaired by German Chancellor Helmut Kohl agreed on 
further budget cuts of 5 billion German marks [DM] in Bonn this 
evening. According to initial information, around DM1.2 billion 
is to be cut from the defense budget. Further cuts were also 
envisaged in the budgets of the Transportation and Labor 
Ministries. German Finance Minister Theo Waigel refused to give 
journalists further details. 

</TEXT>

