<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Slovene Border Charges Halt Aid Convoy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2001200194 Vienna ORF Television Network in German 1830 
GMT 20 Jan 93 </F>

<F P=103> AU2001200194 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna ORF Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Yesterday morning three trucks from Trade for 
Aid, the Salzburg relief organization, set out for Split [in 
Croatia]. However, the transport of 20 tonnes of donated 
foodstuffs, medicine, and winter clothing was halted at the 
Slovene border. Trade for Aid was not able to pay the 137,000 
schillings Slovenia wanted for the 100-km passage. [passage 
omitted] 
  The Salzburg relief organization had all the necessary 
documentation for the aid shipment to the refugee campaigns. 
International relief organizations such as the Red Cross or 
Caritas, and thus the Neighbor in Need campaign, are not 
affected by these Slovene charges. 

</TEXT>

