<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Telecommunications Group Sets Up Joint Ventures in PRC </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2001163894 Paris AFP in English 1526 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2001163894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Paris, Jan 20 (AFP) -- The French Alcatel 
telecommunications group has set up two joint venture companies 
in China with the Chinese Telecommunications Ministry in Beijing 
and Chengdu, the company said on Thursday [20 January]. 
  Alcatel China and the ministry would have equal shares in 
the 
companies set up to work on equipment for transmission by 
Hertzian wave and by cable. 
  The first of these, called Alcatel of Beijing Transmission 
Systems, would produce and distribute Hertzian transmission 
equipment and portable equipment of the same type for the 
Chinese market. 
  The second, Alcatel of Chengdu Communication Systems, would 
produce and distribute cable transmission equipment for the 
Chinese market. 
  The Chinese market in these sectors is believed to be worth 
one billion dollars during the next five years, Alcatel said. 
  The Chinese telecommunications infrastructure grew by 40 
percent between 1992 and 1993, the company said. 
  Alcatel is a leader on the Chinese market for digital 
transmission equipment, holding 50 percent of the market. 
  France and China put their relations on a normal footing on 
January 12 following a period of tension which ended with a 
decision by France to cease selling weaponry to Taiwan. 

</TEXT>

