<H3> <TI>   Police Seize Record 1.2 Tonnes of Cocaine </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2001133094 Paris AFP in English 1247 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2001133094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Toulouse, France, Jan 20 (AFP) -- French police 
said Thursday they had seized a record 1.2 tonnes of cocaine 
with a street value of 170 million dollars after carrying out 
two raids in this south-western region of France. 
  Two-thirds of the drug was found late Wednesday [19 January] 
in an isolated house at Villefranche-de-Lauragais, near here and 
the remainder in the Narbonne area, police said. Three Italian 
nationals were arrested. 
  The cocaine, of Colombian origin, appeared to be headed for 
the Italian market, police said. 

</TEXT>

