<H3> <TI>   Turkish Side To Discuss Confidence-Building Measures </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2001114694 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1130 GMT 20 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2001114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Rauf Denktas has announced that the 
Turkish Cypriot side has agreed to discuss the 
confidence-building measures without making any concessions on 
the principles it has defended so far. 
  The Council of Ministers met under President Denktas at 0900 
today. Upon emerging from the meeting at 1130, the president 
said the Council of Ministers discussed the confidence-building 
measures and reached a decision which will be conveyed to the UN 
secretary general. Denktas pointed out that after the decision 
is conveyed to Secretary General Butrus-Ghali, the necessary 
announcement will be made to the public. 
  In turn, Prime Minister Hakki Atun said the experts will 
continue to study the confidence-building measures. He added 
that work on these measures will be conducted in cooperation 
with President Denktas and the Turkish Republic. The Republican 
Assembly and the other parties will be briefed on the issue, he 
said, adding: The issue will be conducted in unity, taking into 
consideration the interests of the community and the state. 
  The Council of Ministers meeting continued under Prime 
Minister Atun after Denktas left it. The meeting is still in 
session. 

</TEXT>

