<H3> <TI>   UK Foreign Secretary Arrives on Official Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1901161194 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1600 
GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1901161194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] The foreign ministers of Turkey, Britain, and 
Germany will hold a tripartite consultative meeting in Ankara 
tomorrow. Douglas Hurd, British secretary of state for foreign 
and Commonwealth affairs, arrived in Ankara today for a working 
visit and to attend the tripartite meeting. 
  Hurd was received at Ankara's Esenboga Airport by Foreign 
Ministry officials. In an airport statement, Hurd said that all 
economic, political, military, and social issues will be 
discussed at the tripartite meeting in Ankara. Pointing out 
that Turkey is a very important country for the European Union, 
Hurd added that the talks will constitute a significant step in 
the development of relations. 
  German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel will also arrive in 
Ankara tonight to attend the consultative meeting of the three 
foreign ministers tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

