<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Comments on European Relations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1901205394 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 2000 
GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1901205394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Douglas Hurd, British secretary of state for 
foreign and Commonwealth affairs, who is currently in Ankara on 
a working visit, has proposed that Turkey should suggest 
practical steps to develop relations with Europe rather than a 
schedule for membership in the European Union. 
  Addressing the Turkish Scientific and Technical Research 
Institute, Hurd remarked that Turkey is becoming increasingly 
closer to Europe. He noted that ways to advance this process 
will be explored during the talks in Ankara. Hurd explained 
that this process will be accelerated if Turkey resolves its 
economic problems such as high inflation and the budget deficit 
as soon as possible. Noting further that Turkey has great 
knowledge and experience concerning its geographical region, 
Hurd declared that Britain understands the struggle waged 
against terrorism and believes that this problem will be 
surmounted within the framework of democracy. 

</TEXT>

