<F P=102>  LD2301102794 Bern Swiss Radio International in English 0900 
GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2301102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern Swiss Radio International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Swiss President Otto Stich has defended the 
government's decision to invite Mr. 'Arafat for talks at the end 
of this month. Mr. Stich said in a newspaper interview that he 
thought Mr. 'Arafat's visit to Bern was a good idea and was in 
line with Switzerland's promised support for Palestinians in the 
Israeli-occupied territories. He pointed out that Mr. 'Arafat 
had now renounced violence, and it was important for Switzerland 
to be briefed on developments in the Middle East peace process. 
During his first official visit to Bern, Mr. 'Arafat will meet 
Mr. Stich and the Swiss Foreign Minister Flavio Cotti. 

