<H3> <TI>   Thousands Demonstrate Against Racism in Vienna </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2301194994 Vienna ORF Teletext in German 23 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2301194994 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna ORF Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] On the first anniversary of the "Sea of 
Lights," a torchlight procession from Vienna's Ballhaus Square 
to St. Stephen's Square was organized by the "SOS Fellow Man" 
group to protest against isolating foreigners, underprivileged, 
and poor people ("Human beings come first"). A total of 5,000 
people participated in the procession. [passage omitted] 
  In St. Stephen's Square, the number of participants 
increased 
to 10,000. During the final rally, writer Johannes Mario Simmel 
warned against newly developing right-wing extremism. He said: 
"The Nazis are on the advance like never before since 1945." He 
said the letter-bomb attacks in Austria are only a "preliminary 
culmination point." [passage omitted]. 

</TEXT>

