<H3> <TI>   Czech Industry, Trade Minister Pays One-Day Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001152894 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1400 
GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2001152894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vladimir Dlouhy, [Czech] minister of industry and 
trade, is on a one-day visit to Austria today. Marie Budhansova 
reports from Vienna: 
  [Begin Budhansova recording] Vladimir Dlouhy, minister of 
industry and trade of the Czech Republic, is in Vienna today at 
the invitation of the Austrian Government. 
  In the morning, Dlouhy met with Victor Klima, minister of 
transport and public works. According to Mr. Fojtik, the 
commercial counsellor of the Czech Embassy, the Austrian side 
was interested in questions connected with supplies of oil and 
gas to the Czech Republic, progress and details of 
privatization, and problems of the Czech metallurgical industry 
where Austrian firms are involved. 
  Minister Dlouhy was briefed by his hosts on the 
privatization 
of Austrian state industry -- above all the OeMV company, which 
is entering the Czech market -- and ways to achieve guarantees 
with regard to industrial investments and Austrian exports. At 
a joint discussion, he exchanged views and experiences with 
Austrian state sector businessmen. 
  Minister Dlouhy also met today with Vice Chancellor Busek 
and 
Economic Affairs Minister Schuessel. The ambassadors of the two 
countries were present. Dloughy is to end his one-day visit to 
Vienna by paying a courtesy call on Chancellor Vranitzky. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

