<F P=100> PORTUGAL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Bans Movement of Libyan Assets </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2201002394 Lisbon Radio Renascenca in Portuguese to Europe 
0000 GMT 22 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2201002394 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon Radio Renascenca </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Portuguese Government has banned -- except with 
special prior permission from the Bank of Portugal -- the 
movement of any funds in Portugal belonging to or controlled 
directly or indirectly by the Libyan Government, public 
authorities, or companies. This decision is contained in a 
Finance Ministry release published in the official state 
gazette. The release also bans the use of any other funds or 
financial resources in Portugal by the abovementioned bodies. 
These measures will remain in force as long as the UN Security 
Council's sanctions are in force. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

