<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia To Release Information About Nuclear Accidents </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2101115694 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1100 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2101115694 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Finland and Russia have reached a preliminary 
agreement that the threshold for relaying information about 
nuclear accidents will be lowered. Finland will thus receive 
information from Russia about less serious accidents on the 
other side of the eastern border. In addition, the countries 
agreed this week that exchanges of information about nuclear 
plants will be increased. Within the next few weeks a Finnish 
group of experts will visit the Chelyabinsk nuclear waste 
reprocessing plant. 

</TEXT>

