<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mentese Issues Statement on January Operations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2301121794 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1100 
GMT 23 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2301121794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over still of Interior Minister Nahit </F>
Mentese] 
  [Text] Interior Minister Nahit Mentese has announced that 
during operations conducted throughout the country from 1 to 23 
January, 197 terrorists were killed and 707 were captured. In a 
statement issued today, Mentese reported that of these 
terrorists, 176 were killed and 422 captured in the state of 
emergency region. Mentese said that during these operations, 
security forces seized 169 rifles, 63 pistols of various 
calibers, 268 bombs, and 7,224 rounds of ammunition. 
  Stressing that in no country in the world have terrorist 
organizations overpowered the state forces, Mentese remarked 
that in Turkey, too, terrorist organizations will be buried in 
the dark pages of history as a result of the determined and 
dedicated struggle waged by security forces. The interior 
minister said that the state is the counterpart of movements 
directed against the country's integrity and the principles of 
the republic, regardless of where these movements originate 
from. These movements will be stopped and the matter will be 
resolved with speed, Mentese added. He declared: We will 
overcome this nuisance of terrorism with the help of our great 
people and we will certainly bring about an atmosphere of 
tranquillity and security, which our people long for. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

