<H3> <TI>   EU Presidency Issues Statement on Nagorno-Karabakh </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1801144994 Brussels RAPID Database in English 18 Jan 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1801144994 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels RAPID Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [EC press release No. PRES/94/2: "Communique by The </F>
Presidency in The Name of The European Union on The Situation in 
Azerbaijan"] 
  [Text] The European Union is deeply concerned at the fact 
that large-scale fighting has been going on again in the 
Nagorno-Karabakh region since mid-December. 
  It would request the opposing parties to display 
self-control 
and not inflict further suffering on a civilian population 
already sorely tried by the war. 
  It reaffirms its support for the principle of the 
territorial 
integrity of Azerbaijan and calls for a peaceful solution to the 
conflict. Given the danger of internationalization, which could 
aggravate the situation, it would urge the parties concerned to 
cease fighting and implement the relevant resolutions of the 
United Nations security council. 
  The European Union requests the opposing parties to resume 
current negotiations immediately under the aegis of the CSCE 
Minsk group and fully backs those negotiations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

