<H3> <TI>   Socialist Leader Welcomes Clinton's Speech </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1201101694 Brussels EUROPE in English 11 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1201101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels EUROPE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Jean-Pierre Cot Welcomes Clinton's </F>
`Important Political Message'"; as released by Brussels TEXTLINE 
database] 
  [Text] In response to the speech by U.S. President Bill 
Clinton on relations between Europe and the United States, the 
Socialist leader in the European Parliament, Jean-Pierre Cot, 
welcomed the "important political message" of the speech. 
Concerning the opening of the Community market to products from 
East Europe, however, he stressed that this must be a gradual 
process as "we cannot afford to get into a major economic and 
social crisis by opening up completely our trade to East 
European countries just as the United States cannot afford to do 
so." Mr. Cot feels that Europe has already "done more than its 
share and the American side could do a bit more." 

</TEXT>

