<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Upgrades PLO Representation in Bonn </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1901172494 Hamburg DPA in German 1642 GMT 19 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1901172494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- The German Government has upgraded the 
status of the unofficial representation of the Palestine 
Liberation Organisation (PLO) in Bonn. This was confirmed today 
by the German Foreign Ministry. It said the `Palestinian 
Information Office' will be upgraded to the rank of `Palestinian 
Delegation General' [General-Delegation], following the visit to 
Bonn by PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat in December 1993. 
  'Abdullah Franji, the long-term PLO spokesman and the new 
delegate general, will be entitled in the future to raise the 
Palestinian flag in front of his office headquarters in the Bonn 
government district, but will not enjoy diplomatic immunity nor 
other privileges which are reserved for regular embassies. The 
`Delegation General' and its staff will, however, be included in 
the `List of Diplomatic Missions and Other Representations' 
issued by the Foreign Ministry. 
  For its part, the German Government intends to set up a 
German representation -- officially a German aid coordination 
office -- as Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel announced during 
'Arafat's visit. 

</TEXT>

