<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Accuse Munich Man of Working for Stasi </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1701124494 Hamburg DPA in German 1200 GMT 17 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1701124494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Karlsruhe (DPA) -- The investigating judge of the 
Federal Court of Justice (BGH) has issued an arrest warrant for 
a 51-year-old businessman from the Munich area on suspicion of 
espionage activity. The Federal Prosecutor's Office announced 
in Karlsruhe today that the man, who is alleged to have spied 
for the former GDR for at least 11 years, has been in 
investigative custody since 14 January. 
  The accused is said to have supplied the former GDR Ministry 
of State Security (MfS) with computer hardware and software as 
well as files on military technology. The "betrayed extensive 
and valuable material" is said to have been handed over during 
at least 80 meetings on the highway to Berlin. 
  According to the Karlsruhe authority the accused was in 
regular secret service contact with the science and technology 
section of the MfS Main Administration from 1978 to November 
1989. The Federal Prosecutor's Office has commissioned the 
Federal Criminal Investigations Office (BKA) with the 
investigations. 

</TEXT>

