<H3> <TI>   NCC Claims Responsibility for Bomb Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1101113494 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 2244 GMT 10 
Jan 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1101113494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Bomb at NATO Offices in Rome"] </F>
  [Text] Rome, 10 Jan (ANSA) -- A caller to the Neapolitan 
daily IL MATTINO claimed that the Nuclei Communist Combattants 
(NCC) were responsible for the two-kilogram bomb which exploded 
outside the NATO Command Defense College offices in Rome shortly 
after midnight Sunday [9 January] evening. 
  The caller said other sites had been targeted in various 
Italian cities, including the La Brera railway car plant in 
Pozzuoli, some ten kilometers outside Naples. 
  Police were investigating the credibility of the claim that 
the NCC was responsible, a group which has boasted of other 
attacks in the past. 

</TEXT>

