<H3> <TI>   Taipei, Brussels To Form `Quarantine Task Force' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2001101594 Taipei CNA in English 0752 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2001101594 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By P.C. Tang and Y.C. Tsai] </F>
  [Text] Brussels, Jan. 19 (CNA) -- Taiwan and Belgium have 
decided to form a "quarantine task force" to facilitate 
bilateral agricultural trade, the Taipei Economic and Cultural 
Office in Brussels announced Wednesday [19 January]. 
  Problems involving inspection and quarantine practices have 
stood in the way of farm trade between Taiwan and Belgium, a 
spokesman for the office pointed out, adding Belgian traders 
have been longing to sell fresh flowers to Taiwan. 
  The quarantine task force will be composed of officials from 
Belgium's Ministry of Agriculture and Taiwan's Council of 
Agriculture, the spokesman said. 
  Meanwhile, he noted, the first meeting of the task force 
will 
be held in Taipei in April or May. 

</TEXT>

