<F P=100> BENELUX </F>
<F P=101> Belgium </F>
<H3> <TI>   To Simplify Visa Procedures </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2001103594 Taipei CNA in English 0755 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2001103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By P.C. Tang and Y.C. Tsai] </F>
  [Text] Brussels, Jan. 19 (CNA) -- The Belgian Government's 
decision to further simplify visa procedures for Taiwan 
businessmen and tourists will certainly help boost ties between 
the two countries, a spokesman for the Taipei Economic and 
Cultural Office in Brussels said Wednesday [19 January]. 
  Belgium's Ministry of Foreign Affairs sent a notice to all 
its consular offices on January 10 announcing new visa measures 
for Taiwan visitors, the spokesman noted. 
  Under the new measures, Taiwan tourists or businessmen will 
be issued visas at the Belgian Trade Association in Taipei. 
  And when applying for a Belgian visa in a third country, 
Taiwan visitors who were granted a visa in the previous two 
years will be processed without the need for approval by 
Belgium's Foreign Ministry. 
  Earlier, the Brussels government simplified visa procedures 
for Taiwan students who want to pursue advanced studies in 
Belgium. 

</TEXT>

